      "label": "The Portrait Hall",
      "detail": {
        "tier": "clue",
        "text": "Edmund's portrait hangs midway down the hall — with two empty spaces beside it, framed and waiting. Not one. Two. The will, painted on a wall, hiding in plain sight since before anyone thought to look.",
        "flag": "seen_two_portrait_spaces"
      },
      "ref": "III.24"
    },
    {
      "id": "height_marks",
      "at": [1500, 620],
      "kind": "chekhov",
      "label": "A Doorframe",
      "detail": {
        "tier": "character",
        "text": "Two columns of childhood height-marks up the doorframe, 'J' and 'C', climbing year by year — and ending the same year. The house measures its children together or not at all."
      },
      "ref": "III.24"
    },
    {
